{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Plan how API-failure retry termination bound and stopping condition will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f06e12e6a722544bf","ff64707493e88352e","fbdb8f0bd518cb8bb"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"API-failure retry termination bound and stopping condition"},{"coaching":"Run a quick pre-mortem on operator calibration loop exit and abandon criteria: how could this plan fail?","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f0dcd507dbb5eeb8c"],"move_id":"3","move_name":"pre-mortem","subject":"operator calibration loop exit and abandon criteria"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":8,"blocking":0,"dropped":14,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":15,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","probed":6,"ran":true,"references":6,"resolved":2,"status":"pass","unresolved_or_abstained":4},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":15,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":7196,"file_impact":3,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":0,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":15,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"pass","verify_commands_linted":85,"verify_lint_abstained":85},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":1808,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":3,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":197.4,"llm_calls":28,"llm_ms":553026.1,"total_ms":553354.0,"verify_requests":23},"remediation":{"baseline":"signature","eligible":false,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":false,"plan_changed":true,"prior_sidecar":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"signed":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","G7","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","G5","T2","T4","T5b","T5e","T6","T7","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify in the Approach that `test_project_portability_eval.py::finding_contract` must implement custom assertions (not relying on `validate_eval_spec`) to verify that each `expected_counterexample` mapping is non-empty and contains all four required sub-fields (`plan_citation`, `alternate_shape`, `causal_mechanism`, `observable_breakage`).","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["`validate_dataset_and_gold` (eval.py lines 228-272) validates only `id`, `expect`, and the presence of a payload field — it has no logic for `expected_counterexample` or its sub-fields.","Searching `src/rebar/llm/evals/` for `expected_counterexample`, `plan_citation`, `alternate_shape`, `causal_mechanism`, `observable_breakage` returns zero matches.","The plan states 'use the real eval loader plus `validate_eval_spec`' for structural tests, but `validate_eval_spec` is unaware of these fields and will pass a dataset case whether or not they are present.","YAML metadata keys that `validate_dataset_and_gold` does not recognise as payload fields (line 249: `if not any(k not in metadata_keys and case.get(k) for k in case)`) may be silently ignored."],"finding":"The `expected_counterexample` metadata sub-fields (`plan_citation`, `alternate_shape`, `causal_mechanism`, `observable_breakage`) are novel corpus-authoring fields that have no counterpart in the existing `validate_eval_spec` / `validate_dataset_and_gold` framework, yet the plan asserts the `finding_contract` AC can be proved by `test_project_portability_eval.py` using 'the real eval loader plus `validate_eval_spec`'.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f8f8e6463eba75ad4","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Approach section — 'Each must-fire case … records `expected_counterexample` metadata with non-empty `plan_citation`, `alternate_shape`, `causal_mechanism`, and `observable_breakage` fields'; AC line: 'Every must-fire case defines non-empty plan-citation, alternate-shape, causal-mechanism, plus observable-breakage gold fields. Prove with … -k finding_contract'","norm_id":"nbc92c9b0243dd1e3","priority":0.44,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["The `finding_contract` test is authored assuming `validate_eval_spec(strict=True)` will catch missing `expected_counterexample` fields — but it won't, so the test either does nothing or requires custom assertion logic the plan never specifies.","A dataset case is committed with an empty `plan_citation` value and passes `validate_eval_spec` without error, leaving the AC falsely green."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Define the exact validation rule for `expected_counterexample` subfields co-located with the schema description in the Approach (e.g., specify that each of the four subfields must be a non-empty string, and that the `finding_contract` test checks this via a concrete assertion like `all(case['expected_counterexample'].get(f) for f in ('plan_citation','alternate_shape','causal_mechanism','observable_breakage'))`).","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'records `expected_counterexample` metadata with non-empty `plan_citation`, `alternate_shape`, `causal_mechanism`, and `observable_breakage` fields'","validate_dataset_and_gold (eval.py:222-250) has metadata_keys = {'id','corpus','expect','criterion','kind','pair','mode','note','label'} — 'expected_counterexample' is not listed, so it counts as a payload field (vacuous pass). Subfield validation is absent.","No existing eval spec uses expected_counterexample; the schema is entirely novel with no prior-art implementation hook.","AC says 'Prove with … -k finding_contract' but specifies no implementation path for validating nested subfield non-emptiness."],"finding":"The plan defines a novel `expected_counterexample` metadata schema (four required subfields: `plan_citation`, `alternate_shape`, `causal_mechanism`, `observable_breakage`) for must-fire dataset cases, but no processing rule or validator for this schema exists or is specified co-located with the dataset contract. `validate_dataset_and_gold` only checks that a case has any key outside `metadata_keys` — `expected_counterexample` (a dict) satisfies that vacuously. The `finding_contract` test is expected to validate non-emptiness of all four subfields, but no implementation path for this validation is defined in the plan.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f104dad4603c3ffbf","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Approach section — 'Each must-fire case … records `expected_counterexample` metadata'; AC 'Prove with … -k finding_contract'","norm_id":"n33a48613915db92e","priority":0.44,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer authors PORT-F1 with expected_counterexample containing empty strings for some subfields — validate_eval_spec passes, finding_contract test passes (if the test only checks key presence), but the schema contract is silently violated.","An implementer writes the finding_contract test to only check that the key exists (not that all four subfields are non-empty) — the AC is satisfied but the calibration record is incomplete."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add to the Approach: 'The `finding_contract` test asserts that for each PORT-F* case, `case[\"expected_counterexample\"]` is a dict and each of the four named subfields is a non-empty string (len > 0). This is validated directly against the loaded YAML, not via `validate_eval_spec`.'","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Confirm whether `expected_counterexample` metadata (plan_citation / alternate_shape / causal_mechanism / observable_breakage) needs to be a structured sub-object — if its purpose is documentation only, replace with a single `note` string (already in the existing metadata_keys set) or inline the rationale in the `input` text, so no new unread schema is introduced.","cohort":["A1"],"criteria":["A1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["grep for `expected_counterexample`, `plan_citation`, `alternate_shape`, `causal_mechanism`, `observable_breakage` returns zero hits in src/, tests/, or .rebar/evals/ (only a cached plan-review result mentions them)","Only analogous metadata sub-field: `checklist_expect` in plan-review-finder.eval.yaml:379, consumed by test_plan_review_evals.py:250 — one existing call-site, already below Rule-of-Three","`validate_dataset_and_gold` (eval.py:202-272) reads: id, expect, corpus, criterion, kind, pair, mode, note, label, input — `expected_counterexample` is not in the metadata_keys set and not validated","`calibrate_criterion` (eval.py:384-489) only reads `case.get('expect')` and `case.get('id')` from each case — the four sub-fields are inert YAML"],"finding":"The plan introduces a novel four-field metadata schema (`expected_counterexample` with sub-fields `plan_citation`, `alternate_shape`, `causal_mechanism`, `observable_breakage`) for must-fire dataset cases, but zero call-sites exist in the codebase that read, validate, or enforce these fields. The only analogous sub-field convention is `checklist_expect` (one site: `plan-review-finder.eval.yaml` line 379, consumed at `test_plan_review_evals.py` line 250). This new schema meets neither the Rule-of-Three (0 existing readers) nor YAGNI — the calibration goal is already served by the `input` text, and `validate_dataset_and_gold` / `calibrate_criterion` / `run_eval` / every scorer ignore these fields entirely.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f8a67fa8d8c159759","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Approach section: 'records `expected_counterexample` metadata with non-empty `plan_citation`, `alternate_shape`, `causal_mechanism`, and `observable_breakage` fields'; AC: 'Every must-fire case defines non-empty plan-citation, alternate-shape, causal-mechanism, plus observable-breakage gold fields'","norm_id":"n6930f43cf57dc2a4","priority":0.4125,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["The `finding_contract` test will assert these fields are non-empty in YAML, but no runtime path enforces them — they are documentation markers with test-only enforcement, decoupled from the actual evaluation machinery.","Future maintainers adding new portability cases may not know to populate these fields, since nothing outside the new test file consumes them."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Replace `expected_counterexample: {plan_citation: ..., alternate_shape: ..., causal_mechanism: ..., observable_breakage: ...}` with a single `note: |` block on each PORT-F case (the `note` key is already part of `metadata_keys` in `validate_dataset_and_gold`). The `finding_contract` test then asserts `case.get('note')` is non-empty — one field, no new schema, consistent with existing conventions.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a maximum retry count (e.g., 3 per case epoch), a minimum wait between retries (e.g., exponential back-off starting at 10 s), and a clear stopping condition ('if N consecutive full-run failures occur, halt and file a ticket') to the Approach retry instruction.","cohort":["T5b","T6","T9"],"criteria":["T5b"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'rerun the complete command until all eight cases have exactly three completed epochs' — no max retries, no backoff, no circuit-breaker","No mention of exponential backoff or wait between retries","No fallback/degraded mode if API remains unavailable after N attempts","No observability hook (log, metric, or alert) when a retry is triggered"],"finding":"The 'rerun the complete command until all eight cases have exactly three completed epochs' instruction specifies no maximum retry count, no backoff interval, and no stopping condition, so a persistent API outage or rate-limit produces an unbounded loop with no degraded-mode exit for the calibration step.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f06e12e6a722544bf","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Approach section — 'If any model call times out, returns an API error, or produces a partial result, do not attest the partial output: discard that CLI result and rerun the complete command until all eight cases have exactly three completed epochs.'","norm_id":"nd5f1e44ab756f24d","priority":0.2475,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Anthropic API is throttling or under an outage: operator loops indefinitely with no guidance on when to stop","Rate-limit errors cause rapid successive retries, exhausting quota faster and worsening the outage impact"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Replace the open-ended retry instruction with: 'If a call fails, wait at least 30 s before retrying; after three consecutive full-run failures for the same epoch, stop and escalate — do not loop indefinitely. Record each retry attempt and its error code in the ticket comment alongside the final result.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Define a maximum calibration iteration count (e.g., five prompt revisions) and specify what action to take if the threshold is still not met — for example, escalate to the plan author, widen the scope restriction to allow rubric adjustments, or re-examine the dataset boundary cases.","cohort":["T5b","T6","T9"],"criteria":["T6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["No maximum number of calibration cycles is named","No criterion for when to escalate beyond prompt revision (e.g., reconsider the rubric scope or dataset cases)","The operator-attested AC only requires one passing run — it does not bound how many failing runs are acceptable before a different action is taken"],"finding":"The operator calibration loop ('revise only the prompt and rerun') has no defined abandon/exit condition if the live threshold is never met after multiple prompt revisions, leaving the calibration task open-ended with no escalation or scope-change trigger.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f0dcd507dbb5eeb8c","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Approach section — 'If the threshold is missed, revise only .rebar/prompts/plan-review-project-portability.md and rerun; do not change the generic registry, Pass 2, or Pass 3.'","norm_id":"n9f961a4131d4ab99","priority":0.2475,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["The prompt is structurally mis-specified for the model and no amount of wording changes converges — the operator revises indefinitely","A dataset case has an ambiguous boundary that no single prompt can satisfy, causing oscillating pass/fail across revisions"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a maximum retry count (e.g., 'retry up to N times total') and a stopping condition (e.g., 'if still incomplete after N retries, record the partial state and escalate on the ticket') to the API-failure retry policy.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'do not attest the partial output: discard that CLI result and rerun the complete command until all eight cases have exactly three completed epochs'","No max-retry count, no backoff interval, no escalation (e.g., 'after N retries, record the failure and escalate to the ticket')",".rebar/cache finding already flagged this: 'rerun the complete command until all eight cases have exactly three completed epochs specifies no maximum retry count, no backoff interval, and no stopping condition'"],"finding":"The API-failure retry policy in the Approach has no termination bound: 'discard that CLI result and rerun the complete command until all eight cases have exactly three completed epochs' is an unbounded loop with no maximum retry count, timeout budget, or escalation path. This is a mechanism gap — the protocol can spin forever on a persistent API outage.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ff64707493e88352e","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Approach section — 'If any model call times out, returns an API error, or produces a partial result...'","norm_id":"n326ffecd7b6ff22a","priority":0.2475,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Anthropic API rate-limits the operator; the plan's protocol requires indefinite retry with no cap","A persistent model outage blocks the operator-attested AC indefinitely"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add: 'retry up to 5 times total; if all eight cases still lack three completed epochs after 5 attempts, record the partial results and reopen the ticket for rescheduling.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a maximum retry count and a fallback decision rule to the retry protocol in the Approach (e.g., 'If three consecutive complete reruns all fail to produce eight cases with three epochs, record the failure mode and escalate to the ticket author rather than attesting partial results').","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'do not attest the partial output: discard that CLI result and rerun the complete command until all eight cases have exactly three completed epochs'","No max-retry count is specified","No backoff interval is specified","No fallback action is defined (e.g., 'if three consecutive reruns all fail, escalate to operator judgment')","The operator-attested AC 13 provides no alternative completion path"],"finding":"The plan's retry instruction — 'do not attest the partial output: discard that CLI result and rerun the complete command until all eight cases have exactly three completed epochs' — is an unbounded loop with no stopping condition, no maximum retry count, and no fallback for a persistent failure mode (e.g., sustained API outage or a model that never completes all eight cases).","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fbdb8f0bd518cb8bb","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Approach section — 'If any model call times out, returns an API error, or produces a partial result…'","norm_id":"ndbb2b8d6d5a742fa","priority":0.2475,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A transient API outage causes repeated failures across many retries; the operator has no stopping rule and no protocol for when to declare the run unattestable.","One of the eight cases consistently times out due to prompt length; the retry loop never terminates because the condition 'all eight cases have exactly three completed epochs' cannot be satisfied."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an AC (or inline doc update) to extend `src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/README.plan-review.md` with the new corpus-authoring contract: the eight-case balanced structure, `expected_counterexample` metadata schema, and `gold_set` requirements.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T7","T5e"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Use the existing project eval override path proven by src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/README.plan-review.md' — the README is cited as prior art but no update to it is planned","Absence of any doc-update step in the plan's task list or ACs","The expected_counterexample schema (plan_citation, alternate_shape, causal_mechanism, observable_breakage) is a new metadata contract not defined anywhere in existing docs"],"finding":"The plan introduces a novel corpus-authoring contract (gold_set structure, expected_counterexample metadata with plan_citation/alternate_shape/causal_mechanism/observable_breakage fields, and the eight-case balanced-dataset pattern) but proposes no update to src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/README.plan-review.md or any other doc/ADR to capture this new pattern. Future criterion authors will have no canonical reference for how to author a calibration corpus.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3c03ea7d3279eac8","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Approach section — 'expected_counterexample metadata' and 'gold_set' design; src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/README.plan-review.md (referenced but not updated)","norm_id":"n9f4a38cc8c3a285b","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A second engineer authors a calibration corpus for a different criterion and must reverse-engineer the schema from this YAML file rather than reading a spec"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add one AC: 'README.plan-review.md is updated to document the corpus-authoring pattern: balanced 4F/4N dataset, expected_counterexample fields (plan_citation, alternate_shape, causal_mechanism, observable_breakage), and gold_set shape.' This keeps the doc co-located with the override-path documentation the plan already treats as canonical.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7143,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Either add `tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py` to the Scope section (and describe what it tests) or replace the proving command with one that uses only in-scope artifacts (e.g. a grep/jq check against the rubric YAML itself).","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6","F1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Scope section lists only `.rebar/evals/plan-review-project-portability.eval.yaml`, `.rebar/prompts/plan-review-project-portability.md`, `tests/unit/test_project_portability_eval.py`, and the live eval runner — `test_project_portability_criterion.py` is absent.","AC 15 prove command: `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py tests/unit/test_project_portability_eval.py`","Defect taxonomy item (9): 'references a sibling ticket's files with no dependency edge'"],"finding":"AC 15's proving command references `tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py`, a file that does not appear in the Scope section and is never described as something this plan creates. If the file does not exist, the proving command silently fails or errors, leaving the criterion unverifiable.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f83e8efbf2bc8bcbd","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — last bullet ('The final project rubric retains every structural marker…')","norm_id":"nf7c356fd96f620b4","priority":0.11,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An executor runs the proving command and gets a 'file not found' / collection error, making AC 15 structurally unverifiable.","A reviewer cannot confirm the rubric is stable because the test file guarding it is not part of this ticket's deliverables."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add `tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py` to the Scope bullet list with a one-sentence description (e.g. 'validates that the rubric prompt retains the required structural markers'), or change the provi